{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-opus-4-8","id":"msg_011CcwaEwamLD9c5iVUiaMsw","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"toolu_01H9hYwm5MbUqDB15z9Bpopt","name":"Write","input":{"file_path":"/Users/davidlayson/.claude/projects/-private-tmp-phase2-rundirs-594d5c68-with-lessons-ledger--ll2-r1/memory/ci-fixture-race-shared-file.md","content":"---\nname: ci-fixture-race-shared-file\ndescription: Intermittent CI test failures here have been caused by a race in fixture setup on a shared file\nmetadata:\n  type: project\n---\n\nAn intermittent CI test failure (2026-07-11) was root-caused to a race condition in fixture setup: parallel tests touched a shared file without synchronization. Fixed by adding a lock around the shared-file access.\n\n**Why:** It cost the user a full afternoon to find — the failure only surfaced when parallel runs interleaved badly, so it looked like random flakiness rather than a setup bug.\n\n**How to apply:** When triaging intermittent/flaky CI failures in this project, suspect fixture setup first — specifically shared state (files, temp dirs, ports, DBs) touched by tests running in parallel. Check for missing locking/isolation before chasing the test body itself.\n"},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":2,"cache_creation_input_tokens":923,"cache_read_input_tokens":20504,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":923},"output_tokens":3,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"df136cb7-d9b4-4356-935d-4b8f424660e5","uuid":"589548c5-2965-44a4-81b5-4dce8fe7835c","request_id":"req_011CcwaErQDjkVSMGqrtkSxd"}
